<h1>Indicative Home Loan Payout Figure requests</h1>
</sub_heading>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">
<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/processes/default.aspx">Back to Processes</a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">A request to order an indicative Home Loan Payout Figure for Home/Investment Home Loans and Viridian Lines of Credit can be made as follows:</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 1020px;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th style="width: 180px;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Step</span></th>
<th style="width: 844px;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Description</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; width: 180px; background-color: #BFBFBF;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">1</span></td>
<td style="width: 844px; background-color: #BFBFBF;"><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Complete all relevant sections of the <a adhocenable="false" href="https://www.commbroker.com.au/content/dam/commbroker/private/commbroker-forms/Request%20for%20Pay%20Out%20Figure.pdf" target="_blank">Request for Payout Figure form (005-192)</a> and e-mail to <a href="mailto:BrokerAssist@cba.com.au">Broker Assist</a></span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Important</b> - When you send the e-mail to Broker Assist ensure you note in the "Subject" line that it's a Payout figure request and include the customer's name to avoid processing delays.</span></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; width: 180px;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">2</span></td>
<td style="width: 844px;"><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Where the Payout Figure reason is Full Early Repayment Adjustment, Partial Early Repayment Adjustment, Repaid in Full or Property Sold then Broker Assist will return a Payout figure within 4 business hours by return e-mail.</span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Where a Viridian Line of Credit is involved the payout figure will be returned via e-mail the next business day.</span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Note - </b>The PDF copy of the payout figure can be provided to the customer.</span></p> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align: center; width: 180px; background-color: #BFBFBF;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">3</span></td>
<td style="width: 844px; background-color: #BFBFBF;"><p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Where the Payout Figure request reason is External Refinance you should advise the customer that our Customer Retention Unit (CRU) will contact the customer the next business day to discuss their needs and options and also provide the payout figure.</span></p> <p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Note</b>: for Company/Trust payout figure requests Broker Assist will return a pay out figure within 3 business days</span></p>
